>> servings: 30

Set the oven to 175 degrees C.
Mix together @room temperature butter{100%g} with @sugar{90%g}, @vanilla sugar{1%tbsp} and @dark syrup{42%g}.
Mix @flour{150%g} and @baking powder{1%tsp}.
Now fold together both mixes until thoroughly mixed until a dough is formed.
Split dough into three parts and shape each part into a 30 cm long cylinder.
Place all three parts onto a baking sheet and flatten them somewhat using a fork.
Crush some @sea salt{2%tsp} over the dough and then bake in oven for 10-12 minutes.
After baking, remove from oven and let rest for 2 minutes before cutting out the cookies diagonally along the dough.